articles.author: Steve Holland, Joseph Ax, Bianca Flowers, Jarrett Renshaw
articles.description: Donald Trump was elected U.S. president, capping a remarkable comeback four years after he was voted out of the White House and ushering in a new American leadership likely to test democratic institutions at home and relations abroad.
articles.title: Trump secures White House comeback victory, defeating Harris

articles.author: Angelo Amante, John Irish
articles.description: U.N. nuclear watchdog chief Rafael Grossi said on Wednesday he might head to Iran in the coming days to discuss its disputed atomic programme and that he expected to work cooperatively with U.S. President-elect Donald Trump.
articles.title: UN nuclear watchdog chief says he may head to Iran soon as Trump return looms

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Hezbollah chief Naim Qassem said on Wednesday that only developments on the battlefield, not political moves, would bring an end to the hostilities between the Lebanese armed group and the Israeli military.
articles.title: Hezbollah chief says indirect truce talks only possible if Israel stops attacks

articles.author: Ingrid Melander, Krisztina Than
articles.description: European leaders congratulated Donald Trump on Wednesday on his U.S. presidential election victory, saying they were ready to work with him but would defend Europe's interests, amid worries about the impact of a Trump return to the White House.
articles.title: Europe's leaders congratulate Trump, amid worries over trade, Ukraine

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's Premier Li Qiang expressed Beijing's support for Myanmar's political reconciliation and transition efforts in a meeting with Myanmar's junta leader on Wednesday, state media reported.
articles.title: China pledges support for Myanmar's political transition

articles.author: Rachel More
articles.description: The Alternative for Germany, a far-right party polling second nationally, will expel three members arrested for suspected involvement in an extremist group accused by prosecutors of planning an armed revolt, the party said on Wednesday.
articles.title: Germany's far-right AfD party to eject members for suspected links to militant group

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Mexican President Claudia Sheinbaum will wait to formally recognize a winner in the U.S. presidential election until vote tallies are finalized, she said on Wednesday, after preliminary vote results overnight gave Donald Trump a victory.
articles.title: Mexico's Sheinbaum holding off from congratulating winner in US presidential vote

articles.author: Jon Nazca
articles.description: Spanish police have made a record cocaine seizure after finding 13 metric tons of the drug hidden in a shipment of bananas in a container from Ecuador in the southern port of Algeciras.
articles.title: Spanish police seize record cocaine in Ecuadorean banana shipment

articles.author: Cassandra Garrison, Diego Oré
articles.description: Mexico must maneuver carefully now that Donald Trump has secured his return to the U.S. presidency, but Mexico's President Claudia Sheinbaum still has room to negotiate and soften the impact on trade, migration and security.
articles.title: Mexico to feel initial blow from Trump victory but has room to negotiate

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Israeli military said on Wednesday aid organizations had completed a second polio vaccination round for children in Gaza, administering more than 1.1 million vaccinations in different areas of the enclave, achieving 90% coverage.
articles.title: Israeli military says Gaza polio vaccination campaign completed
